1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,000
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

3
00:00:17,949 --> 00:00:20,449
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

4
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:31,213
I think I'm in love with Joon.

5
00:00:39,323 --> 00:00:43,215
I think I've finally met my soulmate.

6
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,325
<i>[Episode 2]</i>
Joon.

7
00:01:21,325 --> 00:01:23,736
How can this food be so delicious?

8
00:01:23,736 --> 00:01:26,230
You know good food.
Do you want some more?

9
00:01:26,230 --> 00:01:27,915
500 won for an extra
bowl of rice, okay?

10
00:01:27,915 --> 00:01:29,852
- I'm in.
- Okay.

11
00:01:34,066 --> 00:01:38,427
This place with my soulmate and
my one and only childhood friend.

12
00:01:39,019 --> 00:01:41,489
This is my true paradise.

13
00:01:53,504 --> 00:01:55,840
You look really surprised.

14
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,563
Did you lose something?

15
00:01:58,459 --> 00:02:03,108
Ah, thank you for letting me
stay over yesterday, friend.

16
00:02:03,108 --> 00:02:05,367
Would you like to eat with us?

17
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:06,805
Friend?

18
00:02:07,953 --> 00:02:10,292
Why didn't you tell me
you were going up?

19
00:02:10,292 --> 00:02:12,730
You disappeared suddenly,
so I was looking for you.

20
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:14,830
You two are still speaking
formally to each another?

21
00:02:14,830 --> 00:02:17,985
Oh, Jae Hoon here isn't very outgoing.

22
00:02:21,181 --> 00:02:25,087
You should put away your blankets if
I allowed you to stay the night.

23
00:02:25,087 --> 00:02:27,155
Of course, my friend.

24
00:02:27,155 --> 00:02:28,983
First, let me have some rice.

25
00:02:28,983 --> 00:02:31,782
Please tidy it up right now.

26
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:37,835
Sure. I can do that, friend.

27
00:02:41,205 --> 00:02:44,532
Hey, did your chairman's son
cause trouble again?

28
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,211
What is wrong with this guy?

29
00:02:47,211 --> 00:02:49,680
What is it? Which one is it?

30
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:52,080
Hey, Kwon Jae Hoon. You're on TV now.

31
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,140
Oh, it's this one.

32
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:57,318
<i>The airplane disturbance case has
caused a great deal of controversy.</i>

33
00:02:57,318 --> 00:03:01,483
<i>Gangsu Group has yet to release
any official statement on the matter.</i>

34
00:03:01,483 --> 00:03:05,455
<i>At this time,
no formal charges have been made.</i>

35
00:03:05,455 --> 00:03:08,133
<i>People are lobbying
to have this case dismissed.</i>

36
00:03:09,074 --> 00:03:10,953
Lobbying to have the case dismissed?

37
00:03:12,794 --> 00:03:14,245
Joon, the thing is...

38
00:03:14,245 --> 00:03:17,902
I guess you'll be busy again taking
care this rich reckless troublemaker.

39
00:03:17,902 --> 00:03:21,173
<i>Reckless troublemaker?</i>

40
00:03:21,173 --> 00:03:22,842
<i>Why am I?</i>

41
00:03:22,842 --> 00:03:24,792
If he was born with
a silver spoon in his mouth

42
00:03:24,792 --> 00:03:26,741
he should be thankful and live quietly.

43
00:03:26,741 --> 00:03:29,353
Where does he get off acting
high and mighty with money?

44
00:03:29,353 --> 00:03:33,188
People like this need to be erased
from the world. They're just evil.

45
00:03:33,188 --> 00:03:37,706
If this guy were in front
of me now... he'd be dead.

46
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:39,665
<i>[Right here.]</i>

47
00:03:40,472 --> 00:03:44,055
Then there's you,
who makes money protecting him...

48
00:03:44,055 --> 00:03:46,602
I'd like to call the stations
and give them a tip.

49
00:03:46,602 --> 00:03:50,925
I'll hold myself back
because I'm very busy with work.

50
00:03:50,925 --> 00:03:52,942
You can do it if you want.

51
00:03:52,942 --> 00:03:56,222
- What?
- Don't hold back. Do what you want.

52
00:03:57,436 --> 00:03:59,270
<i>Troublemaker.</i>

53
00:03:59,270 --> 00:04:02,693
<i>Troublemaker, troublemaker...</i>

54
00:04:02,693 --> 00:04:04,782
- Clean up your blankets.
- <i>Troublemaker...</i>

55
00:04:12,883 --> 00:04:14,235
<i>[Mom]</i>

56
00:04:16,968 --> 00:04:19,793
<i>[Mom]</i>

57
00:04:25,786 --> 00:04:27,716
I'm in despair.

58
00:04:27,716 --> 00:04:29,968
She called me a troublemaker.

59
00:04:29,968 --> 00:04:34,007
Not just reckless, but a troublemaker.

60
00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:36,781
How can she be so mistaken?

61
00:04:36,781 --> 00:04:42,685
This won't do. I need to fix this.

62
00:04:42,685 --> 00:04:45,956
I need to fix this terrible
misunderstanding between me and Joon.

63
00:04:45,956 --> 00:04:48,225
I have made a decision, my friend.

64
00:04:48,225 --> 00:04:50,466
- What decision?
- I'm going to go.

65
00:04:50,466 --> 00:04:56,629
I'll fix this confusing misunderstanding.

66
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:59,728
Don't get involved, don't start trouble.

67
00:04:59,728 --> 00:05:04,100
Go back to the hotel
and stay there, you got it?

68
00:05:20,559 --> 00:05:24,773
No, I've finally met my destiny.

69
00:05:24,773 --> 00:05:27,841
I can't let her think
I'm this reckless troublemaker.

70
00:05:27,841 --> 00:05:32,290
I must prove to her
that I'm not an evil person.

71
00:05:47,812 --> 00:05:49,730
<i>[Gangsu Distribution: Byun Gang Ho]</i>
As for our home shopping site...

72
00:05:49,730 --> 00:05:52,127
we're being inundated
with negative comments.

73
00:05:52,127 --> 00:05:55,463
Of course, sales have gone down
in our mart and department stores.

74
00:05:55,463 --> 00:05:56,923
<i>[Gangsu Foreign Franchise: Byun Geum Hee]</i>
What's the point?

75
00:05:56,923 --> 00:05:59,651
Everyone is already
talking about a boycott.

76
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:03,048
<i>[Gangsu Food Director: Seol Ki Hwan]</i>
If there is a boycott...

77
00:06:03,048 --> 00:06:05,048
it will hurt Gangsu Food the most.

78
00:06:06,072 --> 00:06:08,254
<i>[Gangsu Food President & Group CEO:
Byun Gang Su]</i>

79
00:06:08,254 --> 00:06:10,125
How are the stock prices?

80
00:06:11,266 --> 00:06:13,286
Of course, Gangsu Group's
stock has taken a hit.

81
00:06:13,286 --> 00:06:17,877
Distribution, foreign franchise, and
food have all gone down.

82
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:22,100
We need to start focusing on morals
and family culture from now on, CEO.

83
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:24,923
Why bother talking in circles?

84
00:06:24,923 --> 00:06:26,326
Brother.

85
00:06:26,326 --> 00:06:29,197
Please discipline your son.

86
00:06:29,197 --> 00:06:31,543
Why must we all suffer
because of your son?

87
00:06:31,543 --> 00:06:34,274
President Byun Geum Hee,
this is a professional setting.

88
00:06:34,274 --> 00:06:36,194
Please refrain from
inappropriate comments.

89
00:06:37,437 --> 00:06:40,766
How dare you lecture your aunt?

90
00:06:40,766 --> 00:06:43,774
Why don't you take better care of
your younger brother?

91
00:06:43,774 --> 00:06:45,062
Don't act up with me.

92
00:06:45,062 --> 00:06:48,704
Hey, hey. It's not the first time
Hyuk has caused trouble.

93
00:06:48,704 --> 00:06:50,925
Also, you should cut it out, Geum.

94
00:06:50,925 --> 00:06:52,733
How upset do you think
our older brother is?

95
00:06:52,733 --> 00:06:54,660
How can I cut it out?

96
00:06:54,660 --> 00:06:56,543
Our stock values have
plummeted overnight.

97
00:06:56,543 --> 00:06:59,153
Hey, is it just you? Is it just you?

98
00:06:59,153 --> 00:07:01,593
Who was whining all morning?

99
00:07:01,593 --> 00:07:03,620
Hey! You don't even own that much.

100
00:07:03,620 --> 00:07:05,408
What do you mean I don't own much?

101
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,105
I asked to meet to come up with a plan.

102
00:07:16,105 --> 00:07:18,620
Did I ask to meet to have
an embarrassing family fight?

103
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:22,471
Our stock prices are dropping.

104
00:07:22,471 --> 00:07:26,612
We'll need to come up with
some sort of countermeasure... a plan!

105
00:07:32,384 --> 00:07:34,514
I have a plan.

106
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:09,562
He showed up.

107
00:08:10,622 --> 00:08:12,742
- What?
- He showed up.

108
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,062
The airplane disturbance, the second son.

109
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:23,252
Plan? What plan?

110
00:08:24,283 --> 00:08:26,553
What kind of plan could you have?

111
00:08:28,836 --> 00:08:30,043
I'll turn myself in.

112
00:08:37,019 --> 00:08:40,357
I'll turn myself in
and take my punishment.

113
00:08:40,357 --> 00:08:43,557
I'll make everything
that went wrong, right again.

114
00:08:43,557 --> 00:08:47,302
I'll explain the situation,
so that it doesn't hurt the company.

115
00:08:47,302 --> 00:08:49,692
I will explain it all.
Please leave it to me.

116
00:08:51,687 --> 00:08:53,448
Don't do it.

117
00:08:53,448 --> 00:08:54,467
Excuse me?

118
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:57,164
I don't need you to turn
yourself in or anything.

119
00:08:58,668 --> 00:09:00,621
Just don't do a thing.

120
00:09:01,730 --> 00:09:03,375
But, Father...

121
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:10,586
Who are you to explain anything?

122
00:09:10,586 --> 00:09:13,096
Who would believe anything you say?

123
00:09:13,096 --> 00:09:16,496
Don't say a single word
and don't do anything!

124
00:09:17,606 --> 00:09:21,125
Just do what I tell you to and
go shrivel up somewhere.

125
00:09:22,576 --> 00:09:24,509
Still, I caused the problem
and I should fix...

126
00:09:24,509 --> 00:09:25,677
You punk!

127
00:09:27,447 --> 00:09:30,385
That's right. You did cause the problem.

128
00:09:30,385 --> 00:09:34,297
The bigger problem is that it made
an issue for the whole company.

129
00:09:34,297 --> 00:09:37,857
All because of you,
our company's image was damaged.

130
00:09:37,857 --> 00:09:41,206
Do you know what kind
of loss that created?

131
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:42,336
It's unfair for me too.

132
00:09:42,336 --> 00:09:43,698
Why, you little...

133
00:09:45,716 --> 00:09:49,405
Unfair? What could be unfair for you?

134
00:09:51,249 --> 00:09:54,869
You go around making trouble
without a single thought.

135
00:09:54,869 --> 00:09:56,948
What's unfair for you?

136
00:09:56,948 --> 00:09:58,817
You are the most useless punk.

137
00:09:58,817 --> 00:10:03,299
You are a punk who doesn't
know how to do anything!

138
00:10:11,336 --> 00:10:16,802
<i>All wounds are similar to flowers
and the radiance of flowers.</i>

139
00:10:16,802 --> 00:10:20,327
<i>The wounds that bleed...</i>

140
00:10:20,327 --> 00:10:22,489
<i>give off the fragrance of flowers.</i>

141
00:10:32,418 --> 00:10:35,683
<i>The heart of the person
pierced with the fragrance...</i>

142
00:10:35,683 --> 00:10:38,207
<i>has a large wound.</i>

143
00:10:39,447 --> 00:10:44,138
<i>From that wound,
there was a fragrance of flowers.</i>

144
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,518
Die, you punk! Die!

145
00:10:48,518 --> 00:10:50,259
You little rascal.

146
00:10:52,716 --> 00:10:54,293
I ought to just...

147
00:10:56,505 --> 00:10:57,745
CEO Byun!

148
00:11:34,404 --> 00:11:36,437
Hide him away well.

149
00:11:36,437 --> 00:11:39,725
Put a collar on him or put him in a box!

150
00:11:41,697 --> 00:11:44,086
Make sure he can't get out.

151
00:11:44,086 --> 00:11:46,206
Make sure no one can see him.

152
00:11:58,495 --> 00:11:59,924
Goodness!

153
00:11:59,924 --> 00:12:01,206
Oh, seriously.

154
00:12:30,692 --> 00:12:33,667
My friend... Mon ami.

155
00:12:35,374 --> 00:12:36,990
My friend.

156
00:12:42,024 --> 00:12:43,437
Can you get up?

157
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:46,626
Ow.

158
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:49,687
Oh, this is nothing.

159
00:12:54,197 --> 00:12:55,667
You know my father?

160
00:12:56,885 --> 00:12:58,749
His fists have gotten much weaker.

161
00:13:02,461 --> 00:13:03,995
Maybe that's why...

162
00:13:05,437 --> 00:13:06,855
he's using his feet now.

163
00:13:29,057 --> 00:13:30,268
Hello.

164
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:32,798
- Hello.
- Hello.

165
00:13:32,798 --> 00:13:34,506
Good morning.

166
00:13:41,982 --> 00:13:44,557
Did he go to help that rich troublemaker?

167
00:13:53,613 --> 00:13:55,279
<i>[Mom]</i>

168
00:14:06,977 --> 00:14:09,602
I told you to go to that hotel.
Why did you come here?

169
00:14:11,937 --> 00:14:16,283
I wanted to prove that I wasn't
just a reckless troublemaker.

170
00:14:16,283 --> 00:14:20,596
Chief Byun is doing what he can
to stop you from going to prison.

171
00:14:20,596 --> 00:14:24,581
He wants to buy time as long as
he can and end it with probation.

172
00:14:30,221 --> 00:14:31,764
Hyuk.

173
00:14:31,764 --> 00:14:35,206
There's a car waiting for you in
the parking garage, so go to the hotel.

174
00:14:35,206 --> 00:14:37,346
Don't get caught
by the reporters outside.

175
00:14:37,346 --> 00:14:38,624
In the end...

176
00:14:39,996 --> 00:14:42,684
am I someone who can't
do anything on my own?

177
00:14:45,534 --> 00:14:47,192
Take this.

178
00:14:47,192 --> 00:14:49,486
They might track
your phone, so turn it off.

179
00:14:58,364 --> 00:14:59,437
Let's go.

180
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,139
Get out, get out, get out.

181
00:15:06,139 --> 00:15:07,590
I told you to go!

182
00:15:07,590 --> 00:15:09,831
Hurry up and get out!

183
00:15:09,831 --> 00:15:12,341
I told you, it's good for hangovers.

184
00:15:12,341 --> 00:15:14,490
You said it was good for stamina before.

185
00:15:14,490 --> 00:15:16,692
It's good for stamina and hangovers.

186
00:15:16,692 --> 00:15:18,274
I don't want it either way.

187
00:15:18,274 --> 00:15:20,879
I'm busy so get out. Go, go!

188
00:15:20,879 --> 00:15:24,744
If you don't want it, that's fine.
No need to be like this.

189
00:15:24,744 --> 00:15:27,505
Don't be this way.
Just try it for one month.

190
00:15:27,505 --> 00:15:30,019
I told you I don't want it.
Take it and get out!

191
00:15:30,019 --> 00:15:32,980
You drank all the free ones
I gave you to try last week.

192
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:35,259
You enjoyed the free ones.

193
00:15:35,259 --> 00:15:37,552
Do you take me for a fool?

194
00:15:37,552 --> 00:15:41,149
Hey, Smoothie.
You forcefully gave them to me.

195
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:43,946
Now, you're trying strong-arm me?

196
00:15:43,946 --> 00:15:45,365
- Section Chief.
- Seriously...

197
00:15:54,942 --> 00:15:56,778
It's fine if you don't want it.

198
00:15:56,778 --> 00:15:59,634
How could you throw it all on the ground?

199
00:15:59,634 --> 00:16:01,063
These are for drinking.

200
00:16:01,063 --> 00:16:03,576
Hey, Manager Kim! Call security.

201
00:16:03,576 --> 00:16:05,765
Get this woman out of here now.

202
00:16:05,765 --> 00:16:07,466
This is so annoying,
early in the morning.

203
00:16:14,284 --> 00:16:16,414
Ah, don't let it get to you.

204
00:16:16,414 --> 00:16:19,009
Don't let it get to you, Baek Joon.

205
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,519
Hey, Hyuk.

206
00:16:29,073 --> 00:16:30,821
What do I with these?

207
00:16:34,346 --> 00:16:36,048
Oh, thank you.

208
00:16:42,381 --> 00:16:44,668
Oh, Hyuk!

209
00:16:44,668 --> 00:16:48,495
How... what are you doing here?

210
00:16:48,495 --> 00:16:49,653
Wait.

211
00:16:53,139 --> 00:16:55,381
Hey... huh?

212
00:16:55,381 --> 00:16:56,504
Oh...

213
00:17:11,112 --> 00:17:15,521
Gosh, seriously... who are you?

214
00:17:18,527 --> 00:17:19,818
Oh!

215
00:17:19,818 --> 00:17:23,047
Yes, that's right. Oh... it's me.

216
00:17:23,047 --> 00:17:25,917
How... how did you end up here?

217
00:17:25,917 --> 00:17:29,426
You don't need to know that.
Why don't you just drink it?

218
00:17:29,426 --> 00:17:31,096
How much could it cost in a month?

219
00:17:31,096 --> 00:17:36,294
For a person trying to make a living
and smiling while doing it...

220
00:17:36,294 --> 00:17:38,496
there's nothing
more important than health.

221
00:17:38,496 --> 00:17:41,653
Yes, yes! Ah, yes.

222
00:17:43,217 --> 00:17:45,517
If you really don't have
the money for it...

223
00:17:45,517 --> 00:17:48,153
talk to your team manager,
Kwon, about it.

224
00:17:48,153 --> 00:17:51,449
Yes, I understand.

225
00:17:51,449 --> 00:17:53,911
I'm sorry, Section Chief.

226
00:17:53,911 --> 00:17:56,586
Are you crazy? Let's go.

227
00:17:56,586 --> 00:17:58,067
I'm sorry.

228
00:17:58,067 --> 00:18:00,020
Joon!

229
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:03,486
Hey, you! You, you... hey.

230
00:18:09,887 --> 00:18:14,747
<i>[CEO's troublemaker son,
Byun Hyuk, is in the office.]</i>

231
00:18:15,881 --> 00:18:17,484
<i>[CEO's troublemaker son,
Byun Hyuk, is in the office.]</i>

232
00:18:20,512 --> 00:18:23,826
Please don't post things like this
online, Section Chief Gong.

233
00:18:25,214 --> 00:18:27,394
The company atmosphere
is already quite hectic.

234
00:18:39,794 --> 00:18:42,602
What are you doing?

235
00:18:42,602 --> 00:18:45,542
We're trying to make sales,
not force them into it.

236
00:18:45,542 --> 00:18:46,803
What do you mean force?

237
00:18:46,803 --> 00:18:50,037
I was only trying to make him
understand as a human being.

238
00:18:50,037 --> 00:18:52,018
It looked like you were pressuring him.

239
00:18:52,018 --> 00:18:55,256
Anyway, that's not how you do sales.

240
00:18:57,298 --> 00:19:01,311
Hey... what's wrong with your face?

241
00:19:01,311 --> 00:19:03,463
- Did you get hit?
- Yeah.

242
00:19:06,606 --> 00:19:07,778
Just a bit.

243
00:19:07,778 --> 00:19:09,993
Tell me the truth.

244
00:19:09,993 --> 00:19:11,551
Why did you come here?

245
00:19:14,182 --> 00:19:15,788
The thing about that is, Joon...

246
00:19:15,788 --> 00:19:20,010
To tell you the truth,
my father works here.

247
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:21,785
Where? Which department?

248
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:25,720
Not any department in particular,
but the entire company really.

249
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:28,626
- Is he a laborer?
- Huh?

250
00:19:28,626 --> 00:19:31,803
Like janitorial or security?

251
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:33,479
- Security?
- Oh...

252
00:19:33,479 --> 00:19:35,820
So, he works in security.

253
00:19:37,362 --> 00:19:42,463
If you came to see your father,
why did you get hit like that?

254
00:19:42,463 --> 00:19:45,476
Oh, because of what happened yesterday...

255
00:19:45,476 --> 00:19:48,173
He got very angry because you got
fired from the hotel, right?

256
00:19:48,173 --> 00:19:49,854
- Huh?
- I see.

257
00:19:49,854 --> 00:19:52,424
It's not easy to get a job
like that these days.

258
00:19:52,424 --> 00:19:56,875
From your father's point of view,
I'm sure he's disappointed.

259
00:19:56,875 --> 00:20:00,674
How angry was he that he hit
his son's face like this?

260
00:20:03,053 --> 00:20:07,967
Well... I'm always the son
who disappoints him.

261
00:20:16,414 --> 00:20:18,082
Yes?

262
00:20:18,082 --> 00:20:20,123
You should get back to the hotel.

263
00:20:20,123 --> 00:20:22,188
All right.

264
00:20:22,188 --> 00:20:23,266
I will.

265
00:20:32,756 --> 00:20:35,060
I should get going.

266
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:36,301
Thanks, Joon.

267
00:20:40,854 --> 00:20:42,911
- Hold on for now.
- What?

268
00:20:44,338 --> 00:20:46,805
The police might come around.

269
00:20:46,805 --> 00:20:49,099
It will be investigated
confidentially, so don't worry.

270
00:20:49,099 --> 00:20:51,411
I've already talked it over with them.

271
00:20:51,411 --> 00:20:56,211
By any chance... was this planned
by the prosecutor's office?

272
00:20:56,211 --> 00:20:59,271
We would be in trouble
if this came out too.

273
00:21:00,871 --> 00:21:02,592
Listen carefully.

274
00:21:02,592 --> 00:21:05,584
Since the media knows about it,
we need to make it look good.

275
00:21:05,584 --> 00:21:08,101
If the police find a case there,
it will have credibility.

276
00:21:08,101 --> 00:21:10,546
It will depend, but there
could be an official investigation.

277
00:21:10,546 --> 00:21:13,150
You have to make sure
that doesn't happen.

278
00:21:17,034 --> 00:21:18,324
You have him, right?

279
00:21:20,861 --> 00:21:23,131
Hide him well, so he doesn't get caught.

280
00:21:23,131 --> 00:21:24,803
We can't control it if he shows up.

281
00:21:24,803 --> 00:21:27,799
Gangsu Group is not
the problem. We will be dead.

282
00:21:27,799 --> 00:21:29,845
That's why it's not us, kid.

283
00:21:32,321 --> 00:21:36,140
Then I'll assume that's true
and get going.

284
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:38,551
In my experience...

285
00:21:38,551 --> 00:21:40,770
these things are usually
from someone on the inside.

286
00:21:43,684 --> 00:21:45,919
Enemies are usually someone close by.

287
00:21:56,992 --> 00:22:00,432
Someone on the inside? What do you mean?

288
00:22:00,432 --> 00:22:05,275
Do you still have that
original file that I gave you?

289
00:22:05,275 --> 00:22:10,010
Of course, I put it in my safe
right after you gave it to me.

290
00:22:10,010 --> 00:22:12,259
I'm certain about it so don't worry.

291
00:22:12,259 --> 00:22:14,710
You should make sure that
that flight attendant stays quiet.

292
00:22:14,710 --> 00:22:18,792
It will really be a pain if she starts
giving interviews, crying and so on.

293
00:22:19,784 --> 00:22:20,963
I understand.

294
00:22:22,763 --> 00:22:25,624
Where is Hyuk now anyway?

295
00:22:29,175 --> 00:22:32,005
He's probably at the hotel.

296
00:22:39,227 --> 00:22:42,153
That's the new place
they're building. You see it?

297
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:45,193
Today's the first day,
so they'll be carrying bricks.

298
00:22:45,193 --> 00:22:46,403
There's lots to do.

299
00:22:46,403 --> 00:22:47,957
- Don't worry. Let's go.
- Joon.

300
00:22:47,957 --> 00:22:49,688
- Oh, you're here.
- Joon!

301
00:22:49,688 --> 00:22:51,778
- Is this him?
- Yes.

302
00:22:51,778 --> 00:22:54,429
This is my friend, Byun Hyuk.

303
00:22:54,429 --> 00:22:57,444
He's going through a difficult time.
Please help him out.

304
00:22:57,444 --> 00:22:59,630
Joon, I don't know about this...

305
00:23:04,119 --> 00:23:06,515
He's a little soft. Will he be okay?

306
00:23:06,515 --> 00:23:09,068
What do you mean soft? It's all muscle.

307
00:23:12,128 --> 00:23:15,589
I know he's soft,
but he's got a lot of spirit.

308
00:23:15,589 --> 00:23:18,099
Please teach him well, okay?

309
00:23:18,099 --> 00:23:22,746
- Joon, must I do this?
- All right, since it's you asking.

310
00:23:22,746 --> 00:23:25,836
Hey, get over here Byun.

311
00:23:25,836 --> 00:23:27,605
What do you mean Byun?

312
00:23:27,605 --> 00:23:30,897
Yeah, what is that? Byun?

313
00:23:30,897 --> 00:23:33,397
Mister Byun, follow us.

314
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:38,236
- Byun...
- Joon!

315
00:23:38,236 --> 00:23:39,758
You can make 90,000 won a day.

316
00:23:39,758 --> 00:23:41,746
It's hard to find a job like this.

317
00:23:41,746 --> 00:23:43,945
Don't complain, just learn the job.

318
00:23:43,945 --> 00:23:45,155
See you later.

319
00:23:48,967 --> 00:23:50,023
Joon!

320
00:23:51,236 --> 00:23:53,945
Why are you standing there?
Go work to earn your meal.

321
00:23:53,945 --> 00:23:55,905
Ma'am!

322
00:23:55,905 --> 00:23:57,465
Hurry.

323
00:23:57,465 --> 00:24:00,175
Hurry, hurry. Get going.

324
00:24:02,529 --> 00:24:05,654
You need to put more in there.

325
00:24:05,654 --> 00:24:06,945
Put more.

326
00:24:09,516 --> 00:24:10,672
Get going.

327
00:24:11,885 --> 00:24:14,623
All right. Let's go.

328
00:24:14,623 --> 00:24:17,003
You... you want me to carry this?

329
00:24:17,003 --> 00:24:18,670
Who else would do it?

330
00:24:18,670 --> 00:24:20,753
What are you doing? Hurry up.

331
00:24:22,053 --> 00:24:23,583
Okay. Go.

332
00:24:25,522 --> 00:24:27,736
All right. Go!

333
00:24:27,736 --> 00:24:29,065
Oh, oh. Wait.

334
00:24:29,065 --> 00:24:32,496
All right. Let's go!

335
00:24:34,299 --> 00:24:37,118
Mister Byun, hurry it up.

336
00:24:37,118 --> 00:24:38,465
Ouch.

337
00:24:47,731 --> 00:24:50,857
Hey, Byun. Get over here.

338
00:24:50,857 --> 00:24:51,896
I can't do it.

339
00:24:51,896 --> 00:24:53,142
What do you mean you can't?

340
00:24:53,142 --> 00:24:54,586
Byun Hyuk!

341
00:24:55,743 --> 00:24:57,926
Keep it up!

342
00:24:57,926 --> 00:24:59,618
Stay strong! Woohoo!

343
00:25:00,505 --> 00:25:01,647
Woo!

344
00:25:06,653 --> 00:25:09,304
Ah... I think I'm going crazy.

345
00:25:15,215 --> 00:25:16,336
Hello.

346
00:25:17,660 --> 00:25:21,015
Where are you?
Are you at the hotel?

347
00:25:21,015 --> 00:25:22,777
Jae Hoon, please save me.

348
00:25:22,777 --> 00:25:25,695
- What are you talking about?
- This is hell.

349
00:25:25,695 --> 00:25:28,590
I followed Joon and now I'm
trapped in a part-time job.

350
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:31,710
What? Who did you follow?

351
00:25:31,710 --> 00:25:34,038
Why would you follow Joon?

352
00:25:34,038 --> 00:25:37,018
Please, Jae Hoon. Please save me.

353
00:25:37,018 --> 00:25:38,892
I'm scared and hungry.

354
00:25:38,892 --> 00:25:41,625
You rascal.

355
00:25:41,625 --> 00:25:43,734
Why are you hitting me?

356
00:25:43,734 --> 00:25:46,025
Hello... hello?

357
00:25:52,096 --> 00:25:53,923
He's not picking up.

358
00:25:57,988 --> 00:26:01,015
<i>This caller cannot take your call.</i>

359
00:26:04,919 --> 00:26:07,327
Hey, this is your life around here.

360
00:26:07,327 --> 00:26:09,039
You can't just take it off like that.

361
00:26:09,039 --> 00:26:10,397
Put it back on now.

362
00:26:10,397 --> 00:26:12,445
Why are you doing this to me, Mister?

363
00:26:12,445 --> 00:26:15,666
Why do you think?
I'm taking care of Joon's friend.

364
00:26:15,666 --> 00:26:17,873
You fool around every chance you get.

365
00:26:17,873 --> 00:26:19,001
Where's Joon?

366
00:26:19,001 --> 00:26:21,692
Where do you think?
She's working hard.

367
00:26:29,015 --> 00:26:30,915
<i>Oh my goodness.</i>

368
00:26:30,915 --> 00:26:32,755
<i>That enchanting figure.</i>

369
00:26:32,755 --> 00:26:35,163
<i>Every movement filled with passion.</i>

370
00:26:35,163 --> 00:26:38,324
<i>A natural grace waiting to explode.</i>

371
00:26:38,324 --> 00:26:40,015
<i>Oh, Joon.</i>

372
00:26:40,015 --> 00:26:42,266
<i>You are beautiful
no matter what you are doing.</i>

373
00:26:44,986 --> 00:26:48,586
Hey, hey, hey.
You're drooling.

374
00:26:48,586 --> 00:26:51,046
Wipe your drool and follow me.

375
00:26:51,046 --> 00:26:52,968
What are you doing?

376
00:26:52,968 --> 00:26:54,787
Have you seen the news?

377
00:26:54,787 --> 00:26:56,538
I came because of the video leak.

378
00:26:56,538 --> 00:26:57,675
Are you...

379
00:26:59,496 --> 00:27:01,488
suspicious of me right now?

380
00:27:01,488 --> 00:27:03,828
You just saw me get off the plane.

381
00:27:03,828 --> 00:27:05,297
I wasn't even in the country.

382
00:27:05,297 --> 00:27:07,926
You could've given it to someone else.

383
00:27:07,926 --> 00:27:11,939
You really are just too much.

384
00:27:11,939 --> 00:27:13,733
I'm the victim.

385
00:27:13,733 --> 00:27:17,627
You people didn't take care of it and
now you're coming to threaten the victim?

386
00:27:17,627 --> 00:27:20,887
I hope you understand why I would
have to come talk to you.

387
00:27:20,887 --> 00:27:22,659
I'm doing my best to forget it.

388
00:27:24,717 --> 00:27:27,807
If you continue to come
looking for me regarding this...

389
00:27:27,807 --> 00:27:31,387
I might forget about this settlement.

390
00:27:31,387 --> 00:27:34,969
I hope I don't need to see
your face in the future.

391
00:27:37,198 --> 00:27:39,598
Someone from the media might contact you.

392
00:27:47,220 --> 00:27:49,626
Don't ever agree to an interview.

393
00:27:49,626 --> 00:27:53,749
Keep this a secret from your co-workers
and the people around you.

394
00:27:53,749 --> 00:27:58,170
If you break the contract,
we can breach this settlement, as well.

395
00:27:58,170 --> 00:27:59,198
Goodbye.

396
00:28:16,316 --> 00:28:17,519
Good job.

397
00:28:19,298 --> 00:28:21,568
Good job, young man.

398
00:28:21,568 --> 00:28:22,743
Good work.

399
00:28:23,838 --> 00:28:26,141
You should put some
muscle-healing pads on him.

400
00:28:26,141 --> 00:28:27,868
You're the one who suffered, Mister.

401
00:28:27,868 --> 00:28:29,775
Yeah, I guess.

402
00:28:29,775 --> 00:28:32,382
Hey, you're a young man.

403
00:28:32,382 --> 00:28:35,544
You need more strength.

404
00:28:35,544 --> 00:28:37,232
- Goodbye.
- Yeah.

405
00:28:45,144 --> 00:28:48,460
Ta-da! Today's pay, 90,000 won.

406
00:28:51,226 --> 00:28:54,273
10,000 won is for the lunch
you had earlier.

407
00:28:54,273 --> 00:28:57,056
20,000 won is for the shovel
you broke today.

408
00:28:57,056 --> 00:29:00,153
For the ramen yesterday, I'll give you
a discount since you suffered.

409
00:29:00,153 --> 00:29:04,955
Breakfast was 4,500 won, and tomorrow's
breakfast will be 20,000 won.

410
00:29:04,955 --> 00:29:06,530
Here. Good work.

411
00:29:15,077 --> 00:29:16,323
40,000 won.

412
00:29:18,153 --> 00:29:19,873
Just to earn this...

413
00:29:45,669 --> 00:29:47,721
You don't need to call your dad?

414
00:29:49,259 --> 00:29:53,109
He must feel bad
after hitting you like that.

415
00:29:53,109 --> 00:29:55,167
I told you.

416
00:29:55,167 --> 00:29:59,170
No news is good news
when it comes to me and my father.

417
00:29:59,170 --> 00:30:01,906
I don't know what the issue is.

418
00:30:01,906 --> 00:30:04,530
You should still be good
to him while he's around.

419
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:06,547
It'll be too late once he passes away.

420
00:30:09,101 --> 00:30:11,486
What was your father like?

421
00:30:12,567 --> 00:30:13,656
My dad?

422
00:30:18,941 --> 00:30:20,316
He was a normal man.

423
00:30:22,246 --> 00:30:25,686
He was kind and warm.

424
00:30:25,686 --> 00:30:29,288
He was loving and sensitive.

425
00:30:29,288 --> 00:30:31,671
So, my mom found him
a little bit frustrating.

426
00:30:31,671 --> 00:30:33,458
He was the best dad to me.

427
00:30:35,127 --> 00:30:37,280
If I think about it now...

428
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:40,612
I think he got hurt by the world
a lot because he had so much love.

429
00:30:45,329 --> 00:30:47,471
- So, I...
- Wait, stop!

430
00:30:48,803 --> 00:30:49,920
What is it?

431
00:30:52,451 --> 00:30:55,901
You were about step on
the dandelion seed flower.

432
00:30:57,121 --> 00:30:58,230
Wait.

433
00:30:58,630 --> 00:31:01,279
Here we go.

434
00:31:40,272 --> 00:31:44,170
Whenever I see the dandelion seeds,
I want to let them fly.

435
00:31:45,711 --> 00:31:49,830
It's like a wounded soul
is flying free somewhere.

436
00:31:51,532 --> 00:31:55,871
If they can find root
somewhere new and live there...

437
00:31:55,871 --> 00:31:58,540
they can forget their past bad memories.

438
00:32:27,954 --> 00:32:29,303
Oh, Jae Hoon.

439
00:32:29,303 --> 00:32:31,923
Oh, my friend Jae Hoon.

440
00:32:33,603 --> 00:32:36,750
I guess he's coming home from work.

441
00:32:39,930 --> 00:32:42,800
What are you doing here?
You didn't go home?

442
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:45,459
Oh, the thing is...

443
00:32:45,459 --> 00:32:49,300
He started working a job
with me today. 90,000 won a day.

444
00:32:49,300 --> 00:32:51,500
Yes, 90,000 won a day.

445
00:32:53,001 --> 00:32:54,780
So, that's why I want to ask...

446
00:32:54,780 --> 00:32:58,630
can he stay with you
until he gets his own place?

447
00:32:58,630 --> 00:33:00,409
Can I, Jae Hoon, my friend?

448
00:33:00,409 --> 00:33:03,789
No, just go back to where you belong.

449
00:33:03,789 --> 00:33:07,730
If you don't want to,
then he can stay at my place.

450
00:33:07,730 --> 00:33:09,374
- Really?
- Are you crazy?

451
00:33:09,374 --> 00:33:12,122
I can go sleep downstairs at my
friend's place on the third floor.

452
00:33:13,230 --> 00:33:15,981
But, it'll be 15,000 won a night.
What do you think?

453
00:33:15,981 --> 00:33:17,786
I'll pay for two nights.

454
00:33:23,332 --> 00:33:25,451
Sounds good.

455
00:33:25,451 --> 00:33:27,333
That's good.

456
00:33:27,333 --> 00:33:28,875
Let's go, Joon.

457
00:33:28,875 --> 00:33:30,270
Let's go!

458
00:33:32,938 --> 00:33:35,376
What? I paid already.

459
00:33:35,376 --> 00:33:38,526
What is your problem?
I'm going up to Joon's to sleep.

460
00:33:38,526 --> 00:33:40,448
I paid 30,000 won.

461
00:33:41,601 --> 00:33:42,601
Geez.

462
00:33:42,601 --> 00:33:45,413
Be quiet. Shut your mouth
and and go to bed here.

463
00:33:45,413 --> 00:33:47,832
Joon... Joon!

464
00:33:47,832 --> 00:33:49,521
- Joon!
- Hey.

465
00:33:49,521 --> 00:33:52,432
What? What? My 30,000 won.

466
00:33:55,150 --> 00:33:56,794
My 30,000 won.

467
00:33:57,721 --> 00:33:58,897
Joon.

468
00:33:59,990 --> 00:34:02,071
Joon!

469
00:34:11,614 --> 00:34:14,050
<i>[Mom] </i>

470
00:34:15,882 --> 00:34:17,650
<i>[Mom] </i>

471
00:34:20,858 --> 00:34:22,242
<i>[Mom] </i>

472
00:35:13,293 --> 00:35:14,418
Oh my.

473
00:35:16,588 --> 00:35:17,981
Oh, you scared me.

474
00:35:19,827 --> 00:35:21,918
What is this? Ha Yeon Hee.

475
00:35:25,018 --> 00:35:26,166
It's me.

476
00:35:27,108 --> 00:35:29,233
Look at you just drinking
soju with no food.

477
00:35:30,378 --> 00:35:32,757
You should've called if you were here.

478
00:35:32,757 --> 00:35:34,521
It's not right of you
to drink without me.

479
00:35:34,521 --> 00:35:37,177
I wouldn't do that.

480
00:35:37,177 --> 00:35:40,418
This one is for our pretty Joon.

481
00:35:40,418 --> 00:35:42,443
Thank you very much.

482
00:35:43,969 --> 00:35:46,181
What is it? Something's wrong, huh?

483
00:35:47,257 --> 00:35:48,327
Joon.

484
00:35:49,806 --> 00:35:51,436
Have you seen the news?

485
00:35:52,318 --> 00:35:55,509
Third generation rich guy,
airplane disturbance.

486
00:35:57,382 --> 00:35:59,105
It can't be...

487
00:35:59,105 --> 00:36:01,760
That flight attendant
whose face is blurred out.

488
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:04,023
That person is...

489
00:36:06,047 --> 00:36:07,289
me.

490
00:36:10,438 --> 00:36:11,929
What... what?

491
00:36:16,414 --> 00:36:17,759
My friend.

492
00:36:19,168 --> 00:36:20,570
You see this money here?

493
00:36:23,771 --> 00:36:26,722
It's the first money I earned
shedding blood and tears.

494
00:36:28,530 --> 00:36:32,527
I don't think I'll ever
be able to spend this.

495
00:36:33,710 --> 00:36:35,032
My lucky 10,000 won.

496
00:36:36,813 --> 00:36:38,806
I'll save it as a keepsake.

497
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:42,842
Go ahead and do that.

498
00:36:42,842 --> 00:36:46,210
You won't ever have to do
hard labor to make money again.

499
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,719
Do you know?

500
00:36:48,719 --> 00:36:54,489
Most people can't keep money
as a keepsake after earning it.

501
00:36:54,489 --> 00:36:57,996
They need to eat when they're hungry
and they need shelter to rest in.

502
00:36:57,996 --> 00:37:00,838
A life where income
and spending is equal.

503
00:37:06,106 --> 00:37:08,726
Yes! Hell Joseon.

504
00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:13,518
I feel like Neo,
who just took the red pill.

505
00:37:13,518 --> 00:37:15,677
What are you saying?

506
00:37:15,677 --> 00:37:18,606
The matrix I've been living in
has been shattered.

507
00:37:18,606 --> 00:37:23,295
The woman who gave me the drug
showing me the truth is my destiny.

508
00:37:23,295 --> 00:37:26,358
I really can't just go to sleep.

509
00:37:26,358 --> 00:37:28,025
I need to go have a drink with Joon.

