768
00:56:05,063 --> 00:56:06,340
It's me, Mom.

769
00:56:09,451 --> 00:56:11,202
Have two starting today.

770
00:56:11,202 --> 00:56:14,972
Shouldn't you do that, at least,
considering what you did to me?

771
00:56:14,972 --> 00:56:17,362
Otherwise, I might
really call the police.

772
00:56:25,050 --> 00:56:26,840
Let go of me.

773
00:56:33,641 --> 00:56:35,471
What are you planning to do?

774
00:56:35,471 --> 00:56:38,501
You're not really going
to the police, are you?

775
00:56:38,501 --> 00:56:41,331
Ah, I don't know.

776
00:56:41,331 --> 00:56:43,639
How much will you
give me if I stay quiet?

777
00:56:43,639 --> 00:56:45,728
I need some money quickly.

778
00:56:45,728 --> 00:56:47,179
Are you going to be this way?

779
00:56:47,179 --> 00:56:50,146
Because of that troublemaker
rich guy you work for

780
00:56:50,146 --> 00:56:53,501
I lost my hotel job and
things aren't so good for me.

781
00:56:53,501 --> 00:56:55,349
How much do you want to offer?

782
00:56:55,349 --> 00:56:57,809
How much do you want to offer
for me to keep my mouth shut?

783
00:56:59,802 --> 00:57:03,889
You should know there are many
other ways to do this.

784
00:57:05,507 --> 00:57:08,436
Oh, you're coming on strong.

785
00:57:08,436 --> 00:57:12,286
Why? Will you hurt me if I talk?

786
00:57:12,286 --> 00:57:14,802
Hey, you're not even the victim.

787
00:57:14,802 --> 00:57:17,266
She settled and accepted it.

788
00:57:17,266 --> 00:57:19,367
Do you think you have
the right to act like this?

789
00:57:19,367 --> 00:57:22,608
Social justice and
getting rid of corruption.

790
00:57:23,708 --> 00:57:26,458
I'm thinking I should cut off this
corruption while I can.

791
00:57:26,458 --> 00:57:28,947
I want to make this into a just country.

792
00:57:28,947 --> 00:57:30,306
What do you think?

793
00:57:32,371 --> 00:57:36,778
This is why people need
to walk a careful path.

794
00:57:36,778 --> 00:57:41,628
If employment status is unstable,
society will always act up and complain.

795
00:57:41,628 --> 00:57:44,438
That's the state you're in.

796
00:57:44,438 --> 00:57:45,706
That's correct.

797
00:57:45,706 --> 00:57:49,097
That's why I really
hate rich conglomerates.

798
00:57:49,097 --> 00:57:51,338
It's really funny if you think about it.

799
00:57:51,338 --> 00:57:56,329
Your chairman's son runs away and
society ends up with more power.

800
00:57:56,329 --> 00:57:59,387
The reporters are all waiting
in front of the company today too.

801
00:58:04,601 --> 00:58:05,644
Do you mean it?

802
00:58:05,644 --> 00:58:07,856
- What?
- Money.

803
00:58:07,856 --> 00:58:09,554
Do you really need it?

804
00:58:14,327 --> 00:58:16,815
You're not on the same side.

805
00:58:17,690 --> 00:58:18,786
What do you mean?

806
00:58:23,722 --> 00:58:26,894
He's not going to turn himself in
to the prosecutors, is he?

807
00:58:26,894 --> 00:58:28,619
It's not that he's surrendering himself.

808
00:58:28,619 --> 00:58:31,706
If it's not that, then what?

809
00:58:31,706 --> 00:58:33,760
What is it?

810
00:58:36,052 --> 00:58:37,512
What do you think?

811
00:58:40,047 --> 00:58:41,588
<i>In my experience...</i>

812
00:58:41,588 --> 00:58:43,711
<i>these things are usually
from someone on the inside.</i>

813
00:58:43,711 --> 00:58:46,608
Enemies are usually someone close by.

814
00:58:48,762 --> 00:58:51,108
Where is Hyuk now?

815
00:58:51,108 --> 00:58:53,748
Have you seen him before?

816
00:58:56,987 --> 00:59:01,351
He's the second son of Gangsu Group's
Byun Gang Su, Byun Hyuk.

817
00:59:01,351 --> 00:59:03,568
Do you know him?

818
00:59:03,568 --> 00:59:05,137
Ah, oh...

819
00:59:07,199 --> 00:59:11,634
We got a call that he caused a scene
here and got kicked out.

820
00:59:11,634 --> 00:59:16,574
How could you kick out
a VIP guest like that?

821
00:59:16,574 --> 00:59:19,342
If CEO Byun Gang Su finds out...

822
00:59:19,342 --> 00:59:23,197
that his son was chased out in that
manner, what do you think will happen?

823
00:59:23,197 --> 00:59:25,650
I... I'm sorry.

824
00:59:25,650 --> 00:59:30,210
Our hotel has never kicked anyone out.

825
00:59:30,210 --> 00:59:32,632
- You haven't?
- No. Never.

826
00:59:32,632 --> 00:59:37,581
That kind of unfortunate event
has never happened in our hotel.

827
00:59:37,581 --> 00:59:39,182
- Is that right?
- Of course.

828
00:59:46,693 --> 00:59:47,889
Hello.

829
00:59:51,842 --> 00:59:54,188
You know who I am now, right?

830
00:59:54,188 --> 00:59:55,981
Yes, of course.

831
01:00:09,679 --> 01:00:10,909
Hey, parking.

832
01:00:12,713 --> 01:00:14,304
The police may go looking for him.

833
01:00:14,304 --> 01:00:15,880
Hide him so he doesn't get caught.

834
01:00:15,880 --> 01:00:18,898
We can't fix it if he shows up now.

835
01:00:21,012 --> 01:00:22,869
Can I get a card for my room?

836
01:00:35,592 --> 01:00:38,389
Oh, that's a cool uniform.

837
01:00:38,389 --> 01:00:39,853
That's a great fit.

838
01:00:51,512 --> 01:00:53,387
<i>To his room!</i>

839
01:00:53,387 --> 01:00:54,463
Here you go.

840
01:00:55,670 --> 01:00:56,681
Thank you.

841
01:01:11,190 --> 01:01:13,916
Oops! Oh my, oh my.

842
01:01:13,916 --> 01:01:16,014
I'm so sorry. What can I do?

843
01:01:16,014 --> 01:01:18,101
- I'm sorry.
- This is nothing.

844
01:01:23,409 --> 01:01:26,518
Don't be like that. Just take it off.

845
01:01:26,518 --> 01:01:28,927
I can dry it for you.
It will only take 10 minutes.

846
01:01:28,927 --> 01:01:30,458
Exactly 10 minutes.

847
01:01:48,284 --> 01:01:50,880
I can't do that while I'm on duty.

848
01:01:50,880 --> 01:01:53,007
Goodbye, then.

849
01:01:53,007 --> 01:01:54,101
Excuse me.

850
01:01:56,099 --> 01:01:57,306
Excuse me...

851
01:02:52,724 --> 01:02:54,262
My sweet home.

852
01:02:56,592 --> 01:02:58,972
My sweet home. My sweet home.

853
01:03:38,481 --> 01:03:41,061
Home sweet home. Home sweet home.

854
01:03:44,927 --> 01:03:46,128
This is nice.

855
01:04:16,083 --> 01:04:19,083
Hey... what are you doing?

856
01:04:19,083 --> 01:04:21,673
Keep the car waiting downstairs.
I'll bring him out.

857
01:04:21,673 --> 01:04:23,400
We'll talk details later.

858
01:04:28,094 --> 01:04:32,144
I can't believe things
are over with Joon.

859
01:04:40,574 --> 01:04:42,005
Are you sad?

860
01:04:43,056 --> 01:04:44,275
I'm sad too.

861
01:04:50,409 --> 01:04:51,530
Is that Jae Hoon?

862
01:04:55,382 --> 01:04:57,835
<i>[My Friend, Jae Hoon]</i>

863
01:04:59,304 --> 01:05:01,465
- Yeah, Jae Hoon.
- Hurry up and open the door.

864
01:05:29,804 --> 01:05:33,057
I'm here for your
dry cleaning. Are you inside?

865
01:05:38,224 --> 01:05:39,815
<i>Don't say a word.</i>

866
01:05:50,514 --> 01:05:52,547
Joon, what's going on? Why are you here?

867
01:05:52,547 --> 01:05:54,021
Are you working here again?

868
01:05:54,021 --> 01:05:55,516
- Get inside.
- Inside?

869
01:05:55,516 --> 01:05:57,746
I don't have time to explain. Get inside.

870
01:05:57,746 --> 01:05:59,177
<i>The police are outside.</i>

871
01:05:59,177 --> 01:06:02,059
I think they know you're here.

872
01:06:02,059 --> 01:06:05,179
Joon, you're here to help me?

873
01:06:05,179 --> 01:06:08,733
So, you were worried 
about me, weren't you?

874
01:06:08,733 --> 01:06:11,121
No, I'm here because of money.

875
01:06:11,121 --> 01:06:13,210
- Huh?
- What?

876
01:06:13,210 --> 01:06:15,653
<i>There's a girl?</i>

877
01:06:15,653 --> 01:06:20,846
To put it simply, Hyuk has the fortune
of the folk character, On Dal.

878
01:06:20,846 --> 01:06:22,280
That's what I'm saying.

879
01:06:22,280 --> 01:06:27,949
So, Hyuk needs to be with this
girl in order to become a great man.

880
01:06:27,949 --> 01:06:31,708
She's already close to him,
a girl like Pyung Gang.

881
01:06:31,708 --> 01:06:35,489
I think I'll charge five million won
to get you out. How about it?

882
01:06:39,175 --> 01:06:41,132
No? I'll leave if you don't want to.

883
01:06:48,701 --> 01:06:49,775
I'm in.

884
01:06:53,088 --> 01:06:54,211
What?

885
01:06:55,434 --> 01:06:57,512
I have a condition too though.

886
01:06:57,512 --> 01:06:59,152
What's the condition?

887
01:06:59,152 --> 01:07:03,820
Until I can go home...
will you stay by my side, Joon?

888
01:07:03,820 --> 01:07:05,769
- What?
- Hey.

889
01:07:05,769 --> 01:07:08,675
I have nowhere to go because
the police are following me.

890
01:07:08,675 --> 01:07:11,467
I have to be on the run for now.

891
01:07:11,467 --> 01:07:14,494
I think I'll be less scared
with you by my side.

892
01:07:14,494 --> 01:07:16,764
What kind of crazy things
are you saying?

893
01:07:16,764 --> 01:07:19,994
I'll pay you the average salary
of a Gangsu Group secretary.

894
01:07:21,867 --> 01:07:24,943
You'll work from the time
you wake up until you go to sleep.

895
01:07:24,943 --> 01:07:26,056
What do you think?

896
01:07:34,451 --> 01:07:35,896
Hey, are you insane?

897
01:07:35,896 --> 01:07:38,445
- Who are you...
- My work schedule...

898
01:07:38,445 --> 01:07:40,869
will be 9:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.

899
01:07:40,869 --> 01:07:42,715
- What?
- Okay.

900
01:07:42,715 --> 01:07:45,173
No personal conversation
and no personal chores.

901
01:07:45,173 --> 01:07:47,099
You are not allowed
to pretend we are friends.

902
01:07:48,425 --> 01:07:50,695
Isn't that kind of harsh?

903
01:07:50,695 --> 01:07:52,150
What? You don't like it?

904
01:07:55,231 --> 01:07:57,141
- I'm in.
- <i>Hey.</i>

905
01:07:57,141 --> 01:07:59,202
What are you two doing?

906
01:07:59,202 --> 01:08:01,271
Hello? Hello?

907
01:08:01,271 --> 01:08:03,882
- <i>Hello?</i>
- This is important. Can you be quiet?

908
01:08:03,882 --> 01:08:05,177
What did you say?

909
01:08:10,385 --> 01:08:14,710
Then is today our first day?

910
01:08:18,118 --> 01:08:19,743
Yes, day one.

911
01:08:20,787 --> 01:08:21,966
What? Day one?

912
01:08:32,188 --> 01:08:37,188
Subtitles by DramaFever

913
01:08:54,738 --> 01:08:58,180
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

914
01:08:58,180 --> 01:08:59,829
<i>Even if I needed money...</i>

915
01:08:59,829 --> 01:09:02,220
<i>What if I get arrested too?
I must be crazy.</i>

916
01:09:02,220 --> 01:09:03,917
<i>Mister Byun. You're back.</i>

917
01:09:03,917 --> 01:09:05,425
<i>The oldest son is normal.</i>

918
01:09:05,425 --> 01:09:07,932
<i>It was always the second son
who was the problem.</i>

919
01:09:07,932 --> 01:09:11,069
<i>I heard you were in charge of him.
Where is Byun Hyuk now?</i>

920
01:09:11,069 --> 01:09:13,043
<i>What kind of person is like that?</i>

921
01:09:14,479 --> 01:09:15,851
<i>He looks very elegant.</i>

922
01:09:15,851 --> 01:09:17,292
<i>Is that Joon's boyfriend?</i>

923
01:09:17,292 --> 01:09:19,668
<i>How much do you need?
Tell me. I'll lend it to you.</i>

924
01:09:19,668 --> 01:09:20,979
<i>Forget it. Let's end it with this.</i>

925
01:09:20,979 --> 01:09:22,603
<i>Let's go down our own paths now.</i>

926
01:09:22,603 --> 01:09:24,582
<i>Why does everything I do
end up like this?</i>

